The South African economy grew by 1.1 percent in the first quarter of 2021. This translates to annual GDP growth of 4.6 percent. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African economy grew by 1.1 percent in the first quarter of 2021. This translates to annual GDP growth of 4.6 percent. READ: Stats SA to release Q1 GDP results The finance, mining and trade industries were the main drivers of growth. The figures come just a week after the country's unemployment rate rose to a record 32.6 percent.